The article discusses the opportunities and risks associated with generative AI technology. While AI has the potential to improve people's lives and address societal challenges, it also poses threats to safety, security, civil rights, privacy, and democracy. The author, who has focused on protecting consumers from technology risks throughout their career, highlights the need for collaboration among government, private companies, and society to address these challenges. The author also mentions President Biden's and their commitment to advancing regulations and supporting legislation to ensure the safe and beneficial use of technological innovations. They emphasize the ethical and legal responsibility of private companies to prioritize the safety and security of their products and comply with existing laws. The author looks forward to further discussions and actions in the future.